{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"DiskInjector"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Before the VM boots, "},{"code":"DiskInjector","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" mounts the guest disk image on the host,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"writes a standard macOS LaunchDaemon plist and the user’s script to the data"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"volume, then unmounts. When the VM boots, "},{"code":"launchd","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" picks up the daemon and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"executes the script automatically — no SSH, no agent, no network required."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This uses Apple’s "},{"code":"hdiutil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" (ships with macOS) to attach APFS disk images"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and writes only to the data volume (never the Signed System Volume)."}]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Usage","anchor":"Usage"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["let scriptURL = URL(fileURLWithPath: \"\/path\/to\/setup.sh\")","let bundle = try VirtualMachineBundle.load(from: bundleURL)","try DiskInjector.inject(script: scriptURL, into: bundle)"],"syntax":"swift"},{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"How It Works","anchor":"How-It-Works"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Attaches the guest’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"disk.img","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" using ","type":"text"},{"code":"hdiutil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" without mounting","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(to discover the device node).","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Finds and mounts the APFS data volume from the attached disk.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Writes the user’s script to ","type":"text"},{"code":"\/usr\/local\/bin\/spooktacular-user-data.sh","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"on the data volume.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Writes a LaunchDaemon plist to ","type":"text"},{"code":"\/Library\/LaunchDaemons\/","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" that tells","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"launchd","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to run the script at boot.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Detaches the disk image so the VM can boot cleanly.","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Thread Safety","anchor":"Thread-Safety"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All methods are synchronous and use "},{"code":"Process","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to invoke "},{"code":"hdiutil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Call from a background thread if needed to avoid blocking the main thread."}]}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/diskinjector"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Injects a user-data script into a VM’s guest disk as a macOS LaunchDaemon."}],"sections":[],"metadata":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"DiskInjector"}],"title":"DiskInjector","role":"symbol","externalID":"s:15SpooktacularKit12DiskInjectorO","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"DiskInjector"}],"symbolKind":"enum","roleHeading":"Enumeration","modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}]},"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/Spo